    },
    {
      "file": "src/index.html",
      "description": "# The HTML element\nAfter we declare the doctype, we need to add an `<html>` tag. This tag starts immediately after the doctype. When you close this tag, it should be after all other elements on the page. It's responsible for telling the browser where your HTML markup begins and ends.\n\nIt also tells the browser what language the content is written in using the `lang` attribute. For the purposes of this class, we'll always use english - `en`.",
      "line": 2
    },
    {
      "file": "src/index.html",
      "description": "# The head\nThe `<head>` element is where we put important meta-information about our webpages, and stuff required for our webpages to render correctly in the browser. Never put content that displays on the webpage in this element.\n\nThink of it like your head - it has lots of information about you, but the world can't see what's in your head.",
      "line": 3
    },
    {
      "file": "src/index.html",
      "description": "# Meta tags\nMeta tags tell the browser, search engines, and social media services useful information about the content. Some, like the charset tag, are required for the page to work properly. Others, like description, are optional and used to customize the way your website shows in search results or on social media. \n\nThe description should always be updated in your assignments - think about how to summarize your content to someone who is looking at a search result. In this practice assignment, notice how the content for this description would be helpful to someone seeing a snippet of this content in a Google search.",
      "line": 6
    },
    {
      "file": "src/index.html",
      "description": "# The title tag\n\nThe title element is used to give webpages a human-readable title which is displayed in our webpage’s browser tab. It is also used in search engine results to display the page title. Often, it matches the first heading on the page - the `h1` tag, which we'll see in a moment.\n\nAdd the following title inside the title tag:\n\n```\nCreating Empathy in Notes on Blindness VR\n```",
