      "file": "src/index.html",
      "description": "# The body tag\nThe final element in our HTML boilerplate is the `<body>` element. This is where all the content that will be displayed to users will go - the text, images, lists, links, and so on.\n\nThere is already some content here. Open the linked Google Doc and read it before moving on. When you're done, take a moment to notice how the content is formatted with headings, italics, bold, and links, and how those helped you understand the content more easily and connect to information that was interesting or helpful.\n\nYou can open this link either by copying and pasting the link from this code, or by using `npm run start` in the terminal and clicking the link in the webpage.",
